
*Use examples

# auth to root
sudo su

# create backup
bash savedata-backup.sh -b /etc/savedata/backups.yml -s /etc/savedata/servers.yml --debug

# show status of backups
bash savedata-restore.sh -s ../private/servers.yml --server_name 's1' --backup_name 'pgsql' --status

# restore data 
bash savedata-restore.sh --server_name 's1' --backup_name 'gitreps' --status --debug --restore_path /home/user1/tmp/gitreps/


* Install
== requires ==
sudo apt-get install duplicity
== install  == 
sudo dpkg -i savedata_0.03~beta_all.deb



## Backups ###

== openshift ==
1. At first, you must install rhc;
2. for open rhc without password, read https://help.openshift.com/hc/en-us/articles/202399230-Running-rhc-commands-without-re-entering-password
3. backups.yml block example:

backups:
    ....
    rhc-apps:
        type        : 'rhc'
        <<          : *base
        apps        : ['redmine', 'nexus', 'wiki']
    ....